<Layout
  title="New Concrete Pools Gold Coast | Shotcrete, Block-Render, Freeform | 0485 939 966"
  description="New concrete swimming pool construction on the Gold Coast — shotcrete or block-and-render, freeform / rectangular / infinity edge, pebble / quartz / full-tile interior. QBCC-licensed pool builder."
  canonical="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/services/new-concrete-pools/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Shotcrete, freeform, infinity</span>
      <h1>New concrete pools across the <span class="accent">Gold Coast</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Sprayed shotcrete or block-and-render construction. Freeform curves,
        rectangular lap, infinity edge or beach-entry. Pebble, quartz or
        full mosaic-tile interior. Best for irregular shapes, canal blocks
        and bespoke architectural design. Built to QBCC standards with full
        engineer-certified rebar specification.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61485939966">&#9742; Call 0485 939 966</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Concrete construction methods on the Gold Coast.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Sprayed shotcrete (most common):</strong> Excavate, install rebar cage, spray gunite/shotcrete from a high-pressure nozzle to form the shell, hand-screed and cure. Strongest method, allows any shape. ~$55K&ndash;$220K. Industry default for canal and architectural builds.</li>
          <li><strong>Block-and-render:</strong> Concrete block walls, render-and-waterproof interior. Cheaper, faster, but limited to rectangular and gentle curves. ~$45K&ndash;$80K. Good budget choice for rectangular family pool.</li>
          <li><strong>Cast-in-place reinforced concrete:</strong> Old-school formed concrete. Rarely used now &mdash; shotcrete is superior for almost every case.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Shape language.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rectangular / lap:</strong> Clean modern look, best for serious swimming, easiest to add lane lines. Cheapest. 8m&times;3m to 14m&times;4m typical.</li>
          <li><strong>Freeform:</strong> Curved organic edges, follows the natural landscape. Great for acreage and lifestyle blocks. Adds 15&ndash;30% to cost vs rectangular.</li>
          <li><strong>Infinity edge / knife-edge weir:</strong> One or more edges has zero rim &mdash; water cascades into a hidden trough below. Spectacular for canal and view blocks. Adds $25K&ndash;$60K vs standard.</li>
          <li><strong>Beach entry / zero depth:</strong> Pool gradually rises from 0mm depth to swimming depth. Great for toddlers and dogs. Adds $8K&ndash;$15K.</li>
          <li><strong>Integrated spa:</strong> Spa pocket adjacent to or built into the pool, shared filtration. $12K&ndash;$25K additional.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Interior finishes.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pebble (Pebblecrete, Quartzon, Diamond Brite):</strong> Aggregate-and-cement matrix. Textured grippy surface, 8&ndash;15 year primary lifespan on the Gold Coast (salt accelerates wear). ~$8K&ndash;$14K for an 8m pool. Most common.</li>
          <li><strong>Quartz / Quartzon:</strong> Quartz aggregate, smoother and more durable than pebble. 15&ndash;25 year lifespan. ~$12K&ndash;$20K.</li>
          <li><strong>Full mosaic tile:</strong> Glass or ceramic mosaic over the entire interior. 30+ year lifespan if grout maintained. ~$25K&ndash;$50K for an 8m pool. Premium finish.</li>
          <li><strong>Solid tile:</strong> Larger porcelain or stone tile. Premium architectural look. ~$35K&ndash;$70K.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Build timeline (typical 8m&times;4m rectangular concrete pool).</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Week 1&ndash;2:</strong> Site prep, excavation, dewatering setup if needed, rebar installation.</li>
          <li><strong>Week 3:</strong> Shotcrete spray + curing. Plumbing rough-in.</li>
          <li><strong>Week 4&ndash;6:</strong> Render / waterproof. Coping installation. Tile / pebble interior prep.</li>
          <li><strong>Week 7&ndash;9:</strong> Interior finish (pebble or tile). Fill, balance, commission equipment.</li>
          <li><strong>Week 10&ndash;12:</strong> Surround paving, glass fence, landscaping. Form 23 inspection. Handover.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Engineering &amp; compliance.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Structural engineer-certified rebar plan (cage diameter, spacing, lap)</li>
          <li>QBCC Form 17 lodged with private building certifier</li>
          <li>Hydrostatic-uplift design for low-water-table sites (Coombabah, parts of Helensvale)</li>
          <li>Canal-corridor setback compliance for waterfront blocks</li>
          <li>QDC MP 3.4 / AS 1926.1 barrier integration in design</li>
          <li>Form 23 final Pool Safety Certificate from registered inspector</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

